## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="1cfc4-102">Per impostazione predefinita, <xref:System.Object> vengono effettuato il marshalling di argomenti di tipo come un `VARIANT` tipo, in cui il tipo di oggetto determina il `VARTYPE` pari al `VARIANT`.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1cfc4-102">By default, <xref:System.Object> type arguments are marshaled as a `VARIANT` type, where the object type determines the `VARTYPE` value of the `VARIANT`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="1cfc4-103">Il <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.ErrorWrapper> tipo deve essere passata come un <xref:System.Object> tipo da sottoporre a marshalling come una `VARIANT` di tipo `VT_ERROR`; in caso contrario il <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.ErrorWrapper> tipo viene sottoposto a marshalling come integer.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="1cfc4-103">The <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.ErrorWrapper> type must to be passed as an <xref:System.Object> type to be marshaled as a `VARIANT` of type `VT_ERROR`, otherwise the <xref:System.Runtime.InteropServices.ErrorWrapper> type is marshaled as an integer.</span></span>  
  
